Load JSON descriptions of StriveTogether partnerships

load_partnerships.Rd

Each StriveTogether partnership calculates its CIA report in a slightly different way. Nevertheless, there are many features in common. This function expects a JSON file with an array of objects, one per partnership. The objects contain the details necessary for computing CIA outcomes.

Usage

load_partnerships(.path)

Arguments

.path

<chr> the full path to the partnership

Value

<lst> a named list of partnership information. See Details.

Details

The actual structure of the output depends upon the JSON file. The current expectation is that each object has the following fields.

name <chr>

this will be used as the object's name in the output list.

spreadsheet_id <chr>

the uuid for the Google Sheet that will hold the partnership's results

state <chr>

the two-letter postal code for the state that the partnership works in

state lds info <lst>

an object with whatever info the state-specific function needs to compute outcomes

ipeds unit ids <int[]>

the UNITIDs for each of the partnership's postsecondary collaborators
